race.comment: SISTER DAAE (4) found 1200m a bit sharp when resuming two back then was in the betting but safely held in Saturday company last start over 1400m at Randwick. Looking for this trip third-up and is far better placed back in midweek company. FIORSUM FRED (5) raced handy and tried hard but found a couple better when resuming over 1400m at Newcastle last time out. Has a 60% top three strike rate at or around this distance. Nicely in after Stapleford's claim so certainly worth considering. FAST TRACK (13) led for home and was dominant in a Class 1 over 1400m at Kembla recently. Tougher this time but she is an in-form mare who will give backers a sight. SHANONI (15) went poorly over 1400m at Rosehill last start but is worth another chance back up to this distance. CELLARMASTER (2) did a good job when lining up for just the fourth time in the Listed Magic Millions Guineas last time out. A bad gate with 60.5kgs is a bit of a concern but he is not out of this.
